Algorithm-Voting

This module implements various voting algorithms.  Care has been taken to
thoroughly test these implementations; nonetheless, this code is for
educational and entertainment purposes only--USE AT YOUR OWN RISK.

Currently implemented voting systems:

   Single-winner systems:
      Plurality
      Instant Runoff
      Approval

   Multiple-winner systems:
      Sortition


INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make test
    make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Algorithm::Voting

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Algorithm-Voting

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Algorithm-Voting

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Algorithm-Voting

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Algorithm-Voting


